---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How to Apply | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Apply to a doctoral programme at Brenkley Doctoral College. Check your eligibility, prepare your application, and take the first step towards your doctorate.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Applications</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">How to Apply to Brenkley Doctoral College</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">Applying to a doctoral programme is a significant step. We have designed the process to be clear, supported, and focused on finding the right fit — for you and for us. Applications are welcomed year-round.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Steps -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3 text-center">The Process</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">Four Steps to Your Doctorate</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <div class="card relative">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-accent opacity-20 absolute top-4 right-4">01</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Check Your Eligibility</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-4">Review the entry requirements for your chosen programme. Most Brenkley Doctoral College doctoral programmes require a Master's degree at Merit or Distinction level, significant professional experience, and a preliminary research idea. Some entry points are available for exceptional candidates without a Master's via our Access to Doctorate pathway.</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Master's degree at Merit or above (or equivalent)</li>
            <li>Minimum five years of relevant professional experience</li>
            <li>Outline research idea or area of interest</li>
            <li>English language proficiency (if applicable)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card relative">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-accent opacity-20 absolute top-4 right-4">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Prepare Your Application</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-4">Your application consists of several components that allow us to assess your academic readiness, professional background, and research potential. Take time to prepare these materials thoughtfully — they form the basis of your interview discussion.</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Personal statement (800–1,000 words)</li>
            <li>Research proposal outline (1,500–2,000 words)</li>
            <li>CV including professional and academic history</li>
            <li>Two academic or professional references</li>
            <li>Copies of relevant degree certificates and transcripts</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card relative">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-accent opacity-20 absolute top-4 right-4">03</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Submit Your Application Online</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-4">Submit your completed application through our online portal. Applications are reviewed by our admissions team within ten working days. You will receive an acknowledgement immediately upon submission, and a detailed response confirming whether we are progressing your application to interview.</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Online portal, available 24/7</li>
            <li>Upload supporting documents in PDF format</li>
            <li>Application fee: £75 (non-refundable)</li>
            <li>Acknowledgement within 24 hours</li>
            <li>Full review within 10 working days</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card relative">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-accent opacity-20 absolute top-4 right-4">04</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Interview and Offer</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-4">Successful applicants are invited to an online interview with two members of the academic team, typically including your prospective supervisor. The interview lasts approximately 45 minutes and explores your research proposal, professional background, and motivations. Offers are made within five working days of interview.</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Online interview via video call (45 minutes)</li>
            <li>Discussion of research proposal and methodology</li>
            <li>Opportunity to ask questions about the programme</li>
            <li>Conditional or unconditional offer within 5 working days</li>
            <li>Enrolment deposit required to secure your place</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Entry Requirements -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Requirements</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Entry Requirements</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-accent">DBA / EdD / Online PhD</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Academic:</strong> Master's degree at Merit or Distinction, or equivalent professional qualification at Level 7</li>
            <li><strong>Professional:</strong> Minimum 5 years senior professional experience</li>
            <li><strong>Research:</strong> Preliminary research proposal demonstrating awareness of the field</li>
            <li><strong>English:</strong> IELTS 6.5 overall (if English is not your first language)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-accent">Extended Advanced Diploma (Year 1 of the PhD)</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Academic:</strong> Bachelor's degree at 2:1 or above, or equivalent</li>
            <li><strong>Professional:</strong> Relevant professional experience considered</li>
            <li><strong>Research:</strong> Short research statement (500–800 words)</li>
            <li><strong>English:</strong> IELTS 6.0 overall (if applicable)</li>
            <li><strong>Internship:</strong> Bring your own employer as your placement host, or apply for a match through our <a href="/programmes/mphil/#internship" class="text-accent underline">employer network</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-accent">Access to Doctorate</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Academic:</strong> Bachelor's degree, or significant professional portfolio</li>
            <li><strong>Professional:</strong> Demonstrated commitment to research and professional development</li>
            <li><strong>Research:</strong> Brief statement of research interests</li>
            <li><strong>English:</strong> IELTS 6.0 overall (if applicable)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card mt-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Applying as an Organisation?</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-4">If you want to register an employee for Year 1 of the PhD, or bring forward a project that needs a researcher, this is a separate route from individual applications above.</p>
        <a href="/connect/" class="btn-outline">Discuss a Partnership</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to Expect -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">After You Apply</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What to Expect</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-accent flex-shrink-0">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Acknowledgement</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">You will receive an automated confirmation of your submission immediately. A member of our admissions team will follow up within two working days to confirm that all documents are in order.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-accent flex-shrink-0">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Academic Review</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Your application is reviewed by the Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise and a potential supervisor. They assess your academic background, the clarity of your research proposal, and the fit between your interests and our supervisory capacity.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-accent flex-shrink-0">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Interview Invitation</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">If your application is successful at review stage, you will be invited to an online interview. We aim to offer interview slots within three weeks of application receipt, with flexible scheduling to accommodate international time zones.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-accent flex-shrink-0">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Offer and Enrolment</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">A successful interview leads to a formal offer letter. Conditional offers may require confirmation of qualifications or references. Once conditions are met, you receive an unconditional offer and can proceed to enrolment and induction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to begin?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Explore our programmes to find the right fit, then start your application. If you have questions, our admissions team is happy to help before you apply.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/programmes" class="btn-primary">Explore programmes</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us first</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
